24506.action_text: Proportional to the number of all patients This means that if there are not enough units in the inventory to treat all patients, available units are proportionally allocated among urgent and non-urgent patients.

24510.action_text: Prioritize urgent patients This means that all of the urgent patients will be treated first, and if there are any units left in the inventory, non-urgent patients will be treated.

24522.action_text: Order based on reliability The total order amount will be divided proportionally between suppliers based on their reliablity percentage which is the number of times that orders have been fully satisfied in the past 10 weeks.

24526.action_text: Order equal amount The total order amount will be divided equally between suppliers.

24669.action_text: How would you like to split this amount between suppliers? Total order: {OrTobe} Remaining: {temp} Distributor 1 Distributor 2

25026.action_text: If you are concerned about suppliers' reliablity in delivering orders on time, you may want to order more than suggested amount to ensure that you can satisfy patients demand.

25042.action_text: If you expect demand to change significantly in the future, you may wish to increase or decrease the order amount.

25051.action_text: If you are concerned about inventory costs, you may want to order less than the suggested amount to decrease inventory costs.
